Dear Daddy,
I’m shattered, but I’m not broken. I’m in pain but I’m at peace knowing you are healed and with God- free from all sickness and disease. All the closure I thought I’d never get, I have now. I got to know you as brother, as a friend, and even deeper as a father. I’m so proud of the man you were, I hope we honored you in a way that makes you as proud as you’ve made me. I know you’re on the WESTSIIIIDEEE of heaven bringing havoc to a spades table! I miss you tremendously, GOD I MISS MY DADDY, but I’ll see you again someday. 
I’ll love you always, your baby girl. 

Thank you to my village for everything. 

Thank you to every person who’s called, text, visited, sent gifts, cards, flowers, dm’s, hugs, food, even a nod of acknowledgment- it means the world to me and I’m grateful. ❤️

Grace, grief, grind and gratitude all mixed in together. ✨

📸 @iamjadonj
